main event: Mr. Norman B. Stevens observed a bright white oval-shaped object traveling at high speed in Sunnyvale, California, on October 8, 1965.
interesting points: The object was described as being the size of a basketball and moving at approximately 500 mph., The object was visible for about 6-8 seconds before it vanished from sight., It made no noise and did not leave a vapor trail., The witness, a reliable electronics engineer, reported the incident while driving on Highway 101., This case remains classified as UNIDENTIFIED by the investigating officer.
witness description: Mr. Norman B. Stevens, age 35, an electronics engineer.
